definition.value: A beta-D-glucosylceramide in which a beta-D-glucosyl residue attached to the primary hydroxyl group of N-docosanoyl-14-methylhexadecasphingosine. It is a metabolite of the nematode Caenorhabditis elegans.

A beta-D-glucosylceramide in which a beta-D-glucosyl residue attached to the primary hydroxyl group of N-tricosanoyl-14-methylhexadecasphingosine. It is a metabolite of the nematode Caenorhabditis elegans.

A sulfonamide resulting from the formal condensation of the sulfonic acid group of 5-(dimethylamino)naphthalene-1-sulfonic acid with the aniline nitrogen of 3-(2-acetamido-1,3-thiazol-4-yl)aniline. It has been reported that by triggering an  endoplasmic reticulum (ER) stress response, HA15 can reduce the viability of melanoma cells without being toxic to normal cells.

A beta-D-glucosylceramide in which a beta-D-glucosyl residue attached to the primary hydroxyl group of N-henicosanoyl-14-methylhexadecasphingosine. It is a metabolite of the nematode Caenorhabditis elegans.

A beta-D-glucosylceramide in which a beta-D-glucosyl residue attached to the primary hydroxyl group of N-tetracosanoyl-14-methylhexadecasphingosine. It is a metabolite of the nematode Caenorhabditis elegans.

A beta-D-glucosylceramide in which a beta-D-glucosyl residue attached to the primary hydroxyl group of N-pentacosanoyl-14-methylhexadecasphingosine. It is a metabolite of the nematode Caenorhabditis elegans.

A beta-D-glucosylceramide in which a beta-D-glucosyl residue attached to the primary hydroxyl group of N-hexaacosanoyl-14-methylhexadecasphingosine. It is a metabolite of the nematode Caenorhabditis elegans.

A beta-D-glucosylceramide in which a beta-D-glucosyl residue attached to the primary hydroxyl group of N-tricosanoyl-15-methylhexadecasphinganine. It is a metabolite of the nematode Caenorhabditis elegans.
A terpenoid with formula C17H18O6, isolated from several species of Paeoniae.
A monoterpene glycoside with formula C23H28O12, isolated from several species of Paeoniae.
A monoterpene glycoside with formula C30H32O13, originally isolated from Paeonia suffruticosa.
A  monoterpene glycoside with formula C30H32O13, isolated from several species of Paeoniae.
An organic heteropentacyclic compound with formula C23H26O10, isolated from several species of Paeoniae.
A monoterpene glycoside with formula C23H28O11, originally isolated from the roots of Paeonia lactiflora.
A monoterpene glycoside with formula C21H34O10, originally isolated from the roots of Paeonia lactiflora.

A monoterpenoid that is hexahydro-1-benzofuran-2-one carrying two methyl substituents at positions 3 and 6 as well as two hydroxy substituents at positions 5 and 6 (the 3R,3aR,5S,6S,7aR-diastereomer).

A cyclic monoterpene ketone that is bicyclo[3.1.1]heptan-2-one which is substituted at positions 4, 6, and 6 by hydroxymethyl, methyl, and methyl groups (the 1R,4S,5R stereoisomer). It has been found in Japanese Paeoniae Radix, which has been used in various Chinese medicinal preparations as an anodyne, sedative, antispasmodic, and astringent.
A resolvin that is docosa-4Z,9E,11E,13Z,15E,19Z-hexaenoic acid which is substituted by hydroxy groups at the 7 and 17 positions as well as an oxo group at the 8-position (the 7S,17S-stereoisomer).
A quinoxaline derivative in which the quinoxaline (1,4-naphthyridine) skeleton is substituted with a carboxy function at C-6 and a methyl group at C-2.
A quinoxaline derivative in which the quinoxaline (1,4-naphthyridine) skeleton is substituted at C-5 with a methyl group.
A resolvin that is docosa-4Z,9E,11E,13Z,15E,19Z-hexaenoic acid which is substituted by hydroxy groups at the 7 and 8 positions as well as an oxo group at the 17-position (the 7S,8R-stereoisomer).
An 18-HEPE that consists of (5Z,8Z,11Z,14Z,16E)-icosapentaenoic in which the 18-hydroxy group has S-configuration.
A polyunsaturated fatty acid that is (6E,8Z,11Z,14Z,16E)-icosapentaenoic acid substituted at positions 5 and 18 by hydroperoxy and hydroxy groups respectively (the 5S, 18S-stereoisomer).
A UDP-N-acetyl-D-galactosamine 4,6-bissulfate in which the anomeric centre of the galactosamine fragment has alpha-configuration.
A UDP-N-acetyl-D-galactosamine 4-sulfate in which the anomeric centre of the galactosamine fragment has alpha-configuration.
An amino disaccharide consisting of N-acetyl-D-glucosamine having a 4-deoxy-alpha-L-threo-hex-4-enopyranuronosyl residue attached at the 3-position.
A hydroperoxy fatty acid that is (14S,15R)-epoxy-(5Z,9E,11Z)-icosatrienoic acid in which the hydroperoxy group is located at position 8S.
A hepoxilin A3 in which the stereocentre at position 8 has S-configuration
A quinoxaline derivative in which the quinoxaline (1,4-naphthyridine) skeleton is substituted with a methyl group at each of positions C-2 and C-3.

A pyrazolopyrimidine that is 4H-pyrazolo[1,5-a]pyrimidin-7-one which is substituted at positions 2, 3, and 5 by benzyl, p-chlorophenyl, and p-nitrophenyl groups, respectively. It is an inhibitor of ADP-ribosylation factor 6 (ARF6), a member of the ADP ribosylation factor family of GTP-binding proteins.
A quinoxaline derivative in which the quinoxaline (1,4-naphthyridine) skeleton is substituted at C-2 with a methyl group.
A quinoline compound in which the quinoline skeleton is substituted at C-2 with a methyl group.
An amino tetrasaccharide consisting of beta-D-galactose, N-acetyl-beta-D-galactosamine, beta-D-galactose and D-glucose residues in a linear (1->3), (1->4), (1->4) sequence.
A semisynthetic monoterpene glycoside obtained by acetylation of the 6'-position of the natural product paeoniflorin.
A monoterpene glycoside that is albiflorin carrying a galloyl substituent at position 6. Isolated from the roots of Paeonia lactiflora.
A monoterpene glycoside with formula C23H28O14S, originally isolated from the roots of Paeonia lactiflora.
A glycosyloxyflavone that is apigenin substituted by a beta-L-glucopyranosyl moiety at position 7 via a glycosidic linkage.
A pentacyclic triterpenoid that is urs-12-ene carrying a carboxy substituent at position 28 as well as five hydroxy substituents at positions 2, 3, 19, 23 and 24 (the 2alpha,3beta stereoisomer).
A lignan that is (-)-matairesinol in which one of the phenolic hydroxy groups has been replaced by a beta-D-glucosyl residue.
An enantiomer of pinoresinol having (+)-(1R,3aR,4S,6aR)-configuration.
A lignan that is tetrahydro-1H,3H-furo[3,4-c]furan-1-one carrying a 4-hydroxy-3-methoxyphenyl substituent at position 4.
A member of the class of phytosterols that is poriferast-5-ene carrying a beta-hydroxy substituent at position 3.
A tricyclic sesquiterpenoid that is 4-methylidenedecahydro-1H-cyclopropa[e]azulene carrying three methyl substituents at positions 1, 1 and 7 as well as a hydroxy substituent at position 7.
A sesquiterpenoid obtained by formal condensation of the carboxy group of aristolochic acid with the hydroxy group of (1R,2Z,6E,10E)-3-formyl-7,11-dimethylcyclododeca-2,6,10-trien-1-ol.
A sesquiterpene lactone with formula C15H22O3 that is isolated from Viola yedoensis and Aristolochia versicolor.
A cyclic terpene ketone that is norcamphor carrying two methyl substituents at position 3.
A bornane monoterpenoid that is isoborneol in which the hydroxy hydrogen has been replaced by a formyl group.
A p-menthane monoterpenoid that is delta-terpineol in which the hydroxy hydrogen has been replaced by an acetyl group.
